{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"An image containing explicit content is flagged and held for review, not published.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Failure boundary is model judgment quality: whether the vision model correctly identifies explicit content. A stubbed classifier would always return the expected label and miss real misclassification failures (MOCK-HIDE, LLM-DEP). I considered Workflow but rejected it because the behavior text describes one model decision plus a deterministic hold/not-publish action, not multiple agentic decisions in sequence.","test_description":"Run a test with real vision-model calls on a curated explicit-image set and assert each submission is held for review and never published.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.75,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"A text post containing hate speech is flagged regardless of obfuscation techniques (e.g., letter substitution, unicode lookalikes).","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"This behavior depends on real text-model robustness to adversarial/obfuscated inputs, which is inherently AI-output dependent (LLM-DEP). Deterministic mocks hide exactly this failure mode. I considered Workflow but rejected it because the behavior targets one classification decision per post, not a multi-step agentic chain.","test_description":"Use real text-model inference on a corpus of obfuscated hate-speech variants (leet, homoglyphs, spacing tricks) and assert they are flagged and held.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.85,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"A post that passes both content checks is published rather than held or silently dropped.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Primary failure is local module handoff/orchestration: combining image+text pass results into the final publish action and ensuring no drop path. In-process wiring with deterministic pass responses is sufficient to expose this. INTEGRATION-BRAKE: (a) no real OS/network/subprocess required; (b) no dependence on model output quality because both checks can be fixed to pass; (c) no multi-agentic sequence required; (d) no LLM-governed stage-handoff correctness beyond deterministic status propagation.","test_description":"Wire moderation orchestrator + decision module + persistence/publish adapter in-process, feed deterministic 'pass' results from both check modules, and assert exactly one published record/event and no hold/drop side effects.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.06,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The full moderation pipeline — image check, text check, publish decision — completes within 5 seconds of submission.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This is a real latency/SLO behavior across external dependencies; mocks will hide network, service, and runtime effects that create true timing failures (REAL-INFRA, MOCK-HIDE). I considered Agentic but rejected it because the pass/fail criterion is end-to-end elapsed time, not model-output quality/non-deterministic judgment.","test_description":"Execute end-to-end submissions against real deployed pipeline dependencies (real HTTP/service calls) and assert p95 completion time from submission to final decision is <= 5s under representative peak-hour load profile.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.09,"System":0.78,"Agentic":0.08,"Workflow":0.04}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the AI vision model is unavailable, image posts are queued for retry rather than auto-approved.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Failure appears at an external availability boundary (timeouts/connection/refusal/